---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | CookTwo" description="Built for couples. Powered by edge computing. CookTwo is a collaborative adaptive nutrition app — one shared kitchen for two people with different dietary goals.">

  <section class="section-padding bg-cream">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <span class="badge-signature mb-6 inline-block">About</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">Built for couples.<br class="hidden md:block" /> Powered by edge computing.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">CookTwo is a collaborative adaptive nutrition app. One shared kitchen for two people with different dietary goals.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">The Problem</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="text-terracotta font-bold">1</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">"What's for dinner?"</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary">The nightly argument. You want healthy, they want easy. You're counting calories, they're not. Two people, one kitchen, zero alignment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="text-terracotta font-bold">2</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">Two people, two goals, one kitchen</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary">One person is losing weight, the other is building muscle. Existing apps treat them as separate users with separate plans. Nobody helps them cook <em>together</em>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="text-terracotta font-bold">3</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">$600/year wasted on food</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary">Duplicate groceries, forgotten pantry items, impulse delivery orders. The average couple household wastes significant money on food that never gets eaten.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="text-terracotta font-bold">4</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">20 minutes scrolling delivery apps</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary">Decision fatigue sets in. You scroll through DoorDash, UberEats, Grubhub. You order something neither of you really wanted. Repeat tomorrow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-cream-dark">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">The Solution</h2>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-sage mb-6">CookTwo: One shared kitchen for two people.</h3>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-sage flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Same meal, different plates</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">One recipe, personalized portions and macros for each partner</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-sage flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Real-time collaboration</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Shared grocery list, shared pantry, shared meal plans — synced instantly</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-sage flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text-primary">AI that knows what you have</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Pantry-first meal suggestions that reduce waste and save money</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-sage flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Built for "we", not "me"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Every feature designed for two people sharing one kitchen</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="badge-live mb-6 inline-block">Tech Architecture</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">The Technology</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">Built on Cloudflare's global edge network. Sub-100ms responses everywhere. Zero cold starts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-sage/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-sage" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="8" x2="16" y1="21" y2="21"/><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="17" y2="21"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">Frontend</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">React 19</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">Vite</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">TypeScript</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">Tailwind CSS</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>PWA with service worker (Workbox) — installable from browser, no app store</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Zustand for client state, TanStack Query for server state</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Offline queue for grocery list changes when connection drops</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-terracotta" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><rect x="2" y="14" width="20" height="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="6" x2="6.01" y1="6" y2="6"/><line x1="6" x2="6.01" y1="18" y2="18"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">Backend</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta font-medium">Cloudflare Worker</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta font-medium">Hono Framework</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>30+ API endpoints for household, pantry, grocery, meal plan, and recipe management</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>JWT authentication with secure token-based sessions</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Multi-provider AI chain with automatic fallback (DeepSeek → Alibaba Qwen → ZAI)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-sage/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-sage" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/><path d="M3 5V19A9 3 0 0 0 21 19V5"/><path d="M3 12A9 3 0 0 0 21 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">Database</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">Cloudflare D1</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">SQLite</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Tables: Households, Partners, Meal Plans, Recipes, Grocery Items, Pantry Items</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Per-household data isolation — no cross-contamination between kitchens</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-terracotta" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">Real-Time</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta font-medium">Cloudflare Durable Objects</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta font-medium">WebSocket</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Per-household WebSocket server — each couple gets their own dedicated real-time connection</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Sub-100ms sync — add milk at home, partner sees it at the store instantly</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>SQLite storage inside Durable Object for grocery/pantry items</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Hibernation when idle — costs nothing when you're not actively syncing</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-sage/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-sage" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2a3 3 0 0 0-3 3v7a3 3 0 0 0 6 0V5a3 3 0 0 0-3-3Z"/><path d="M19 10v2a7 7 0 0 1-14 0v-2"/><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="19" y2="22"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">AI Providers</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">DeepSeek (default)</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">Alibaba Qwen (fallback)</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-sage/10 text-sage font-medium">ZAI (fallback)</span>
            <span class="text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta font-medium">Flux.2 via OpenRouter (images)</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Automatic fallback chain — if DeepSeek is slow, Qwen takes over. If Qwen fails, ZAI handles it.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-sage mt-1">&#8226;</span>
              <span>Flux.2 (Black Forest Labs, via OpenRouter) for AI-generated meal photography</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-cream">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-8 text-center">Built by one person, for two.</h2>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center sm:items-start gap-6">
            <img src="/images/team/barry-profile.webp" alt="Barry, founder and developer of CookTwo" class="w-28 h-28 rounded-2xl object-cover flex-shrink-0 border border-border" loading="lazy" />
            <div class="text-center sm:text-left">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-1">Barry</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-sage font-medium mb-3">Founder, designer &amp; engineer</p>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                CookTwo is designed, built and shipped by one person — frontend, backend, AI integration, infrastructure and design, all from a kitchen table in New Zealand. It grew out of a very real frustration: cooking every night with a partner who has completely different dietary goals, and finding no tool on earth designed to help two people eat from the same kitchen without compromise.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-border grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-sage">1</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">solo founder</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-sage">2</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">plates, always</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-sage">0</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">app stores</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary/70 text-center mt-6 italic">"You're not selling an app. You're selling the end of the nightly argument." — the principle CookTwo is built on.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-8 text-center">Market Position</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-number">$1.8B</div>
            <div class="stat-label">TAM (2025) → $5.2B (2034)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-number">28%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">AI nutrition CAGR</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-number">35M+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">US couple households in target demographic</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 bg-cream rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 md:p-8 text-center">
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Category: "Collaborative Adaptive Nutrition"</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary">CookTwo defines a new category at the intersection of real-time collaboration, adaptive nutrition, pantry-first AI, and relationship-centric design. No existing app occupies this space.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding bg-sage">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ready to cook together?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">One kitchen. Two plates. Zero arguments. Try CookTwo free.</p>
      <a href="/#get-early-access" class="inline-block bg-white text-sage px-8 py-4 rounded-xl text-lg font-semibold transition-colors hover:bg-cream shadow-lg">Get Started Free</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
